'''Khenti-khet''' was the term used in the {{ill|Ancient Egyptian calendar|de|Ägyptischer Kalender|12=draft|12=draft}} for the harvest season and the third month of the {{ill|Shemu|de|Schemu|1=Season of the Harvest|lt=Schemu|12=draft|12=draft}} period. The name '''"The One of the Valley"''' refers to its '''coincidence with the {{ill|Beautiful Festival of the Valley|de|Schönes Fest vom Wüstental|12=draft|12=draft}}'''. From the '''{{ill|Predynastic Egypt|de|Prädynastik (Ägypten)|12=draft|12=draft}}''' until the end of the '''{{ill|Middle Kingdom of Egypt|de|Mittleres Reich (Ägypten)|12=draft|12=draft}}''', Khenti-khet originally represented the '''eleventh month''' of the '''{{ill|Sothic calendar|1=Ancient Egyptian Lunar Calendar|de|Mondkalender (Altes Ägypten)|1=Ancient Egyptian Lunar Calendar#Der ursprüngliche Mondkalender|12=draft|12=draft}}''', covering the period from '''April 1 to April 30'''.

== Background ==

=== Position in the Calendar ===

{{ill|Alan Gardiner|de|Alan Gardiner|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Richard Anthony Parker|de|Richard Anthony Parker|12=draft|12=draft}} suggest that '''Khenti-khet underwent shifts in the calendar system''' over time, which led to its '''placement as the tenth month from the {{ill|New Kingdom of Egypt|de|Neues Reich|12=draft|12=draft}} onwards'''.

In the '''{{ill|Ebers calendar|de|Ebers-Kalender|12=draft|12=draft}}''' (ca. '''1517 BCE'''), '''Khenti-khet''' corresponded to the '''first Shemu month''', falling between:

* '''April 15 – May 14''' ({{ill|Elephantine|de|Elephantine|12=draft|12=draft}})
* '''April 21 – May 20''' ({{ill|Memphis, Egypt|de|Memphis (Ägypten)|12=draft|12=draft}})

The name of the '''third Shemu month''' was later changed to '''{{ill|Epiphi|de|Epiphi|12=draft|12=draft}}'''.

=== Beginning of the Wheat Harvest ===

The '''New Kingdom lunar calendar month {{ill|Paoni|de|Payni|12=draft|12=draft}}''' is recorded in texts from the '''{{ill|Twelfth Dynasty of Egypt|de|12. Dynastie|12=draft|12=draft}}''' under the name '''Khenti-khet''', marking the '''beginning of the wheat harvest'''. Administrative records place it in '''late March to early April''', as part of the '''first month of the {{ill|Peret|de|Peret (Altes Ägypten)|1=Season of the Emergence|lt=Peret|2=de|3=Peret (Altes Ägypten)|4=ja|5=ペレト|6=zh|7=播種季|8=ru|9=Перет|10=uk|11=Перет|13=Season of the Emergence|14=es|15=Estación de la emergencia|16=fr|17=Peret|18=pl|19=Peret|20=ro|21=Peret|12=draft|12=draft}} season'''.

